The two women who carried out the attacks wore explosive belts, presumably using detonation devices set inside their mobile phones and activated by a call to self. [27] The attackers intended to strike during peak hours on a weekday when the subway would be at capacity. Eyewitnesses said that some survivors were so badly injured that they constantly splashed heavy amounts of blood on the floor and walls, until they were attended to by doctors. [28]
Alexander Bortnikov , the FSB chief, said its investigation pointed to "terrorist groups related to the North Caucasus ". [29]
