Cheryl Beckett, aged 32 years, [27] was an aid worker and translator, from Knoxville, Tennessee , United States, and an Indiana Wesleyan University graduate; she had been in Afghanistan for six years and specialized in nutritional gardening and mother-child health. [30] [31]
